  <article class="prose-tool space-y-7">
    <h1>Signature Size for Exam Forms</h1>
    <p>
      Indian exam portals often ask for a scanned signature in JPG format with strict dimensions and a file
      size such as 10KB to 50KB. The exact size depends on the exam notification.
    </p>
    <h2>Common signature settings</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>140 x 60 px for compact forms</li>
      <li>160 x 60 px for many recruitment portals</li>
      <li>200 x 80 px when a clearer signature is allowed</li>
      <li>JPG format under 20KB or 50KB, depending on the portal</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Best scanning method</h2>
    <p>
      Sign on plain white paper using a black or dark blue pen. Crop close to the signature and remove
      extra white space before resizing. Avoid shadows and blurry phone photos.
    </p>
    <p>
      Use <a href="/tools/signature-resize/">Signature Resize</a> to resize and compress your signature for
      exam forms directly in your browser.
    </p>
  </article>
</GuideLayout>
